  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What makeup to wear for red dress?",
  "response": "When selecting makeup to complement a red dress, consider the overall look you want to achieve\u2014whether it\u2019s bold and dramatic or soft and elegant. Here are some ideas to help you create the perfect makeup look:\n\n### Eyes\n1. **Neutral Tones**: Use neutral eyeshadow shades like warm browns or soft taupes to balance the boldness of the dress.\n2. **Smoky Eye**: For a dramatic look, a classic smoky eye using black, charcoal, or deep shades of burgundy can make your eyes pop.\n3. **Bold Liner**: Winged eyeliner can add an elegant touch. Consider using a dark liquid liner to create definition.\n4. **Metallic Accents**: Gold or bronze metallic shadows can add a glamorous sparkle, enhancing the red dress without overpowering it.\n\n### Lips\n1. **Classic Red**: If you want a classic look, go for a matching red lipstick but choose a different shade than your dress to avoid looking too matchy.\n2. **Nude or Pink Lips**: For a softer look, opt for a nude or soft pink lipstick that won\u2019t compete with the dress.\n3. **Glossy Finish**: A gloss can add a modern and fresh touch, especially with a more subtle lip color.\n\n### Cheeks\n1. **Soft Blush**: Use a soft peach or pink blush to add a healthy glow to your complexion without overshadowing the dress.\n2. **Highlighter**: A subtle highlighter on your cheekbones can add radiance and enhance your features, especially if you're opting for a more neutral makeup look.\n\n### Overall Tips\n- **Balance**: If your eye makeup is bold, keep your lips more neutral, and vice versa. This creates a balanced look.\n- **Foundation**: Make sure your foundation is flawless for a polished appearance, as the simplicity of a red dress can highlight any imperfections.\n- **Setting Spray**: Consider a setting spray to keep your makeup in place throughout the evening.\n\nUltimately, choose colors and styles that enhance your features and make you feel confident. Have fun experimenting!",
